v5: there is no variable to change default y-gutter between columns.

```scss
@mixin make-row($gutter: $grid-gutter-width) {
  --bs-gutter-x: #{$gutter};
  --bs-gutter-y: 0;
  // ...
}
```

**--bs-gutter-y** is hardcoded. it would be great to have a variable to change it.

would be nice to have a native svg icons color-support for the nav-bar. it would just required the `fill` command parallel to the `color` command. 

here is how i made it for my site on bootstrap v3:

```
.navbar-inverse {
    .navbar-nav {
        > li > a {
            fill: #9d9d9d;

            &:hover,
            &:focus {
                fill: #fff;
            }
        }
        > .active > a {
            &,
            &:hover,
            &:focus {
                fill: #fff;
            }
        }
        > .disabled > a {
            &,
            &:hover,
            &:focus {
                fill: #444;
            }
        }
    }
}
```

